{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DYnczUxDNFpRmMEnWfkEca","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The snapshot completed successfully. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Status: Complete — no pod restarts needed.**\n\nThe setup was already partially configured:\n- The `es-secure-settings` Secret had `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (both `minioadmin`), and the StatefulSet mounts it — Elasticsearch had already loaded these into its keystore.\n- `elasticsearch.yml` already contained the S3 client settings (endpoint, http protocol, path-style access).\n\n**Steps performed:**\n\n1. **Reloaded secure settings** (`POST /_nodes/reload_secure_settings`) — confirmed all 3 nodes picked up the keystore credentials without a restart.\n\n2. **Registered `minio-repo`** (`PUT /_snapshot/minio-repo`) as an S3 repository pointing at bucket `es-backups` using the `default` client (whose endpoint/credentials come from the keystore and `elasticsearch.yml`).\n\n3. **Verified the repository** — all 3 nodes confirmed connectivity to MinIO.\n\n4. **Created `snapshot-1`** (`PUT /_snapshot/minio-repo/snapshot-1?wait_for_completion=true`) — completed in 600ms with `state: SUCCESS` and zero failures."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":427,"cache_read_input_tokens":34889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":427},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"43c842d7-f109-42e6-b41b-eb36bbe0f18e","uuid":"ad0bb967-a78e-410e-a0a7-f5a993091b00","request_id":"req_011CcQ4qv2ckfE6MHEYDzqSB"}
